<h1>Installing with the Debian-Installer</h1>
 
<if-stable-release release="sarge">
<p>
<b>For official Debian <current_release_sarge> installation media and
information</b>, see
<a href="$(HOME)/releases/sarge/debian-installer">the sarge page</a>.
</p>
</if-stable-release>

<p>
<b>To install Debian testing</b>, we recommend you use
the etch beta 1 release of the installer, after checking its
<a href="errata">errata</a>. The following images are available for
beta 1:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>netinst CD image (100 Mb)<br>
	<netinst-images />
	</li>
	<li>businesscard CD image (50 Mb)<br>
	<businesscard-images />
	</li>
	<li>full CD sets<br>
	<full-cd-images />
	</li>
#	<li>full CD sets (via <a href="$(HOME)/CD/torrent-cd">bittorrent</a>)<br>
#	<full-cd-torrent />
#	</li>
	<li>full <a href="http://cdimage.debian.org/pub/cdimage-testing/cd/beta1/">CD</a>
	and <a href="http://cdimage.debian.org/pub/cdimage-testing/dvd/beta1/">DVD</a>
	sets (via <a href="$(HOME)/CD/jigdo-cd">jigdo</a>)
	</li>
	<li>graphical installer (alpha release)<br>
	[<a href="http://people.debian.org/~fjp/d-i/gtk-miniiso/alpha/amd64/">amd64</a>]
	[<a href="http://people.debian.org/~fjp/d-i/gtk-miniiso/alpha/i386/">i386</a>]
	[<a href="http://people.debian.org/~fjp/d-i/gtk-miniiso/alpha/powerpc/">powerpc</a>]
	<li>other images (netboot, usb stick, floppy, etc)<br>
	<other-images />
	</li>
</ul>

